{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_012jGphNQhPE81vG9EVMvnjT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have all the information I need. Here's the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n### 1. New file: `config/monitoring/prometheus-rule.yaml`\n\nCreate the directory `config/monitoring/` and the PrometheusRule YAML:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\nkind: PrometheusRule\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: prometheusrule\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: monitoring\n    app.kubernetes.io/created-by: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: kustomize\n  name: alerting-rules\n  namespace: system\nspec:\n  groups:\n    - name: multiarch-tuning-operator.rules\n      rules:\n        - alert: MultiarchImageInspectionFailureRateCritical\n          expr: |\n            (\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[10m])\n              /\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[10m])\n            ) > 0.05\n          for: 5m\n          labels:\n            severity: critical\n          annotations:\n            message: >-\n              Image inspection failure rate has exceeded 5% over the last 10 minutes.\n              Gated pods may be stuck waiting for scheduling or falling back to the\n              default architecture. Check registry connectivity and pull secret\n              configuration.\n```\n\n### 2. New file: `config/monitoring/kustomization.yaml`\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- prometheus-rule.yaml\n```\n\n### 3. Modified file: `config/default/kustomization.yaml`\n\nAdd `../monitoring` to the `resources` list so the PrometheusRule is included when deploying:\n\n```diff\n resources:\n - ../crd\n - ../rbac\n - ../manager\n - ../webhook\n+- ../monitoring\n```\n\nThe full file becomes:\n\n```yaml\nnamespace: openshift-multiarch-tuning-operator\nnamePrefix: multiarch-tuning-operator-\napiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1\nkind: Kustomization\nresources:\n- ../crd\n- ../rbac\n- ../manager\n- ../webhook\n- ../monitoring\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key design decisions\n\n- **Metrics used**: `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` (counter) and `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` (counter), as defined in `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/controller.go:58-69`.\n- **Expression**: Matches the alerting PromQL from `agentic/RELIABILITY.md:67-69` — `rate(failed[10m]) / rate(processed[10m]) > 0.05`.\n- **Threshold**: 5% (0.05), the SLO boundary documented in the reliability doc: \"Image inspection success rate > 95%\".\n- **Window**: 10-minute `rate()` window with a 5-minute `for` duration to avoid firing on transient spikes.\n- **Severity**: `critical`, matching the alerting thresholds table in RELIABILITY.md.\n- **Namespace `system`**: Uses the kustomize placeholder namespace, which gets rewritten to `openshift-multiarch-tuning-operator` by the `namespace:` directive in `config/default/kustomization.yaml`.\n\n## Commands to run\n\n```bash\n# Create the monitoring directory\nmkdir -p config/monitoring\n\n# After creating the files above, verify kustomize renders correctly:\nkustomize build config/default\n```\n\nNo `make` targets need modification — the existing `make manifests` and `make deploy` targets use `kustomize build config/default` which will pick up the new resource automatically."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":148,"cache_creation_input_tokens":326,"cache_read_input_tokens":42104,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":326,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e19fb47e-815b-4eb4-9f6b-ec4792b35aba","uuid":"4430d632-8b88-4f87-b21a-e6bf824116a9","timestamp":"2026-07-20T17:06:44.710Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_